page.title: 05HOUSING IN WITHYHAM ST.JOHN
page.content: There are thirteen category 2 listed {buildings.} They are mostly{timber framed, dating from as early as the 15th century. 1. Whitehouse Farmhouse 17th c. 2. Litle Abbots cottage 17th c. 3. Forest Lodge Cottage 18th c. 4. Half Moon Inn,{stone}18th c. 5. Half Moon Cottages 18th c. 6. Hoadley's Farm 16th c. 7. Sackville LOdge/stables 18th c. 8. Bingles, timber &{plaster}15th c. 9. Littlebrook " " " 16th c. 10.Park Grove Farm " " " 16th c. 11.The Forge, timber & brick 17th c. 12.Summsersales Farm,stone 16th c. 13.Friarsgate (Grubb's) Farmhouse Many of these lie along the route of the B2188 and the B210 LOndon Road.
